{
    "type": "success",
    "html": "<div class=\"infinite-wrap infinite-view-4\" id=\"infinite-view-4\" data-page-num=\"4\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Page: 4.\">\n<article id=\"post-53391\" class=\"post-53391 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-abim-exam category-cardiovascular-usmle-step-1 category-cardiovascular-usmle-step-2 category-cardiovascular-usmle-step-3 category-emergency-medicine-shelf category-family-medicine-shelf category-gastrointestinal-usmle-step-2 category-gastrointestinal-usmle-step-3 category-icu-series category-medicine-usmle-step-2 category-medicine-shelf category-organ-systems-usmle-step-3 category-pediatrics-shelf category-pharmacology-usmle-step-1 category-pharmacology-usmle-step-2 category-pharmacology-usmle-step-3 category-podcast category-renal-usmle-step-1 category-renal-usmle-step-3 category-respiratory-usmle-step-1 category-respiratory-usmle-step-2 category-respiratory-usmle-step-3 category-shelf-exams category-usmle-step-1 category-usmle-step-2-ck category-usmle-step-3\">\n\t<header class=\"entry-header\">\n\t\t<h1 class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/11/11/dip-ep-625-the-5-usmle-gaps-step-1-3/\" rel=\"bookmark\">DIP Ep 625: The 5 USMLE &#8220;Gaps&#8221; (Step&nbsp;1-3)</a></h1>\t</header><!-- .entry-header -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n\t\t\t<span class=\"posted-on\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/11/11/dip-ep-625-the-5-usmle-gaps-step-1-3/\" rel=\"bookmark\"><time class=\"entry-date published\" datetime=\"2025-11-11T07:18:00-05:00\">November 11, 2025</time></a></span><span class=\"byline\"><span class=\"author vcard\"><span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><a class=\"url fn n\" href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/author/divineinterventionpodcast/\">divineinterventionpodcast</a></span></span>\t\t\t<span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><span class=\"comments-link\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/11/11/dip-ep-625-the-5-usmle-gaps-step-1-3/#respond\">Leave a comment</a></span>\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-content\">\n\t\t<p>In this podcast, I conceptually explain the 5 different gaps tested on the USMLEs (Serum AG, Urine AG, Osmolal gap, SAAG gradient, and A-a gradient). I make numerous integrations and really help you understand these things so you don&#8217;t have to memorize them. <em><strong>Another point of emphasis (low SAAG ascites is similar conceptually to exudative effusions)</strong></em>. If you&#8217;re interested in the Step 1-3 classes beginning next week, shoot me an email.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-53391-1\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/dip-ep-625-the-5-gaps-on-the-usmles.mp3?_=1\" /><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/dip-ep-625-the-5-gaps-on-the-usmles.mp3\">https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/dip-ep-625-the-5-gaps-on-the-usmles.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/dip-ep-625-the-5-gaps-on-the-usmles.mp3\">Audio Download</a></p>\n\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-content -->\n\t</article><!-- #post-## -->\n\n<article id=\"post-52609\" class=\"post-52609 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-podcast\">\n\t<header class=\"entry-header\">\n\t\t<h1 class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/10/09/dip-ep-624-common-interview-errors/\" rel=\"bookmark\">DIP Ep 624: Common Interview&nbsp;Errors</a></h1>\t</header><!-- .entry-header -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n\t\t\t<span class=\"posted-on\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/10/09/dip-ep-624-common-interview-errors/\" rel=\"bookmark\"><time class=\"entry-date published\" datetime=\"2025-10-09T11:10:07-04:00\">October 9, 2025</time></a></span><span class=\"byline\"><span class=\"author vcard\"><span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><a class=\"url fn n\" href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/author/divineinterventionpodcast/\">divineinterventionpodcast</a></span></span>\t\t\t<span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><span class=\"comments-link\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/10/09/dip-ep-624-common-interview-errors/#respond\">Leave a comment</a></span>\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-content\">\n\t\t<p>In this podcast, I detail common errors applicants make during the course of interviews. Try to avoid these as you navigate the ERAS process.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-52609-2\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/dip-ep-624-common-interview-errors.mp3?_=2\" /><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/dip-ep-624-common-interview-errors.mp3\">https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/dip-ep-624-common-interview-errors.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/dip-ep-624-common-interview-errors.mp3\">Audio Download</a></p>\n\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-content -->\n\t</article><!-- #post-## -->\n\n<article id=\"post-52148\" class=\"post-52148 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-emergency-medicine-shelf category-family-medicine-shelf category-medicine-shelf category-microbiology-usmle-step-1 category-microbiology-usmle-step-2 category-microbiology-usmle-step-3 category-pediatrics-shelf category-podcast category-rapid-review-usmle-step-2 category-shelf-exams category-usmle-step-1 category-usmle-step-2-ck category-usmle-step-3\">\n\t<header class=\"entry-header\">\n\t\t<h1 class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/09/15/dip-ep-623-last-minute-microbiology-review-step-2-and-3/\" rel=\"bookmark\">DIP Ep 623: Last Minute Microbiology Review (Step 2 and&nbsp;3)</a></h1>\t</header><!-- .entry-header -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n\t\t\t<span class=\"posted-on\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/09/15/dip-ep-623-last-minute-microbiology-review-step-2-and-3/\" rel=\"bookmark\"><time class=\"entry-date published\" datetime=\"2025-09-15T08:27:23-04:00\">September 15, 2025</time></a></span><span class=\"byline\"><span class=\"author vcard\"><span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><a class=\"url fn n\" href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/author/divineinterventionpodcast/\">divineinterventionpodcast</a></span></span>\t\t\t<span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><span class=\"comments-link\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/09/15/dip-ep-623-last-minute-microbiology-review-step-2-and-3/#respond\">Leave a comment</a></span>\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-content\">\n\t\t<p>In this podcast, I review a host of HY microbiology factoids that commonly show up on Step 2 and 3. You will directly get many questions right on your exam from listening to this podcast. I make so many integrations and delve into some test taking principles with this.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-52148-3\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dip-ep-623-last-minute-micro-step-2-and-3.mp3?_=3\" /><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dip-ep-623-last-minute-micro-step-2-and-3.mp3\">https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dip-ep-623-last-minute-micro-step-2-and-3.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dip-ep-623-last-minute-micro-step-2-and-3.mp3\">Audio Download</a></p>\n\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-content -->\n\t</article><!-- #post-## -->\n\n<article id=\"post-51941\" class=\"post-51941 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-podcast category-rapid-review-usmle-step-2 category-usmle-step-2-ck category-usmle-step-3\">\n\t<header class=\"entry-header\">\n\t\t<h1 class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/09/05/dip-ep-622-usmle-step-2-3-rapid-review-series-130/\" rel=\"bookmark\">DIP Ep 622: USMLE Step 2/3 Rapid Review Series&nbsp;130</a></h1>\t</header><!-- .entry-header -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n\t\t\t<span class=\"posted-on\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/09/05/dip-ep-622-usmle-step-2-3-rapid-review-series-130/\" rel=\"bookmark\"><time class=\"entry-date published\" datetime=\"2025-09-05T07:43:40-04:00\">September 5, 2025</time></a></span><span class=\"byline\"><span class=\"author vcard\"><span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><a class=\"url fn n\" href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/author/divineinterventionpodcast/\">divineinterventionpodcast</a></span></span>\t\t\t<span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><span class=\"comments-link\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/09/05/dip-ep-622-usmle-step-2-3-rapid-review-series-130/#respond\">Leave a comment</a></span>\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-content\">\n\t\t<p>In this podcast, I discuss a host of cardiac, renal, and heme pathologies that routinely show up on the USMLE exams. I also discuss some tips and pointers on the way the USMLEs love to write questions. Email me via the website if you would love to take my zoom classes this month.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-51941-4\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dip-ep-622-step-2-and-3-rr-series-130.mp3?_=4\" /><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dip-ep-622-step-2-and-3-rr-series-130.mp3\">https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dip-ep-622-step-2-and-3-rr-series-130.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dip-ep-622-step-2-and-3-rr-series-130.mp3\">Audio Download</a></p>\n\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-content -->\n\t</article><!-- #post-## -->\n\n<article id=\"post-51702\" class=\"post-51702 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-podcast category-rapid-review-usmle-step-2 category-usmle-step-2-ck category-usmle-step-3\">\n\t<header class=\"entry-header\">\n\t\t<h1 class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/08/25/dip-ep-621-usmle-step-2-3-rapid-review-series-129/\" rel=\"bookmark\">DIP Ep 621: USMLE Step 2/3 Rapid Review Series&nbsp;129</a></h1>\t</header><!-- .entry-header -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n\t\t\t<span class=\"posted-on\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/08/25/dip-ep-621-usmle-step-2-3-rapid-review-series-129/\" rel=\"bookmark\"><time class=\"entry-date published\" datetime=\"2025-08-25T07:45:45-04:00\">August 25, 2025</time></a></span><span class=\"byline\"><span class=\"author vcard\"><span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><a class=\"url fn n\" href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/author/divineinterventionpodcast/\">divineinterventionpodcast</a></span></span>\t\t\t<span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><span class=\"comments-link\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/08/25/dip-ep-621-usmle-step-2-3-rapid-review-series-129/#respond\">Leave a comment</a></span>\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-content\">\n\t\t<p>In this episode, I spend a lot of time making integrations and discussing some &#8220;often not covered&#8221; mechanisms that show up frequently on the USMLE Step 2/3 exams. Worth your while ahead of your test. If you&#8217;re interested in signing up for the 20 hr Step 2/3 class taking place this week, shoot me an email through the website.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-51702-5\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-621-step-2-and-3-rr-series-129.mp3?_=5\" /><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-621-step-2-and-3-rr-series-129.mp3\">https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-621-step-2-and-3-rr-series-129.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-621-step-2-and-3-rr-series-129.mp3\">Audio Download</a></p>\n\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-content -->\n\t</article><!-- #post-## -->\n\n<article id=\"post-51527\" class=\"post-51527 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-musculoskeletal-and-dermatology-usmle-step-1 category-musculoskeletal-and-dermatology-usmle-step-3 category-podcast category-rapid-review-usmle-step-2 category-usmle-step-1 category-usmle-step-2-ck category-usmle-step-3\">\n\t<header class=\"entry-header\">\n\t\t<h1 class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/08/18/dip-ep-620-usmle-msk-series-knee-hip/\" rel=\"bookmark\">DIP Ep 620: USMLE MSK Series (Knee,&nbsp;Hip)</a></h1>\t</header><!-- .entry-header -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n\t\t\t<span class=\"posted-on\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/08/18/dip-ep-620-usmle-msk-series-knee-hip/\" rel=\"bookmark\"><time class=\"entry-date published\" datetime=\"2025-08-18T10:42:35-04:00\">August 18, 2025</time></a></span><span class=\"byline\"><span class=\"author vcard\"><span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><a class=\"url fn n\" href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/author/divineinterventionpodcast/\">divineinterventionpodcast</a></span></span>\t\t\t<span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><span class=\"comments-link\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/08/18/dip-ep-620-usmle-msk-series-knee-hip/#respond\">Leave a comment</a></span>\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-content\">\n\t\t<p>In this podcast, I continue to delve into MSK concepts the USMLEs consider to be relevant for Step 1-3 by discussing NBME pathologies relating to the knees and hip. Short podcast but very HY for your test.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-51527-6\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-620-usmle-msk-knee-and-hip.mp3?_=6\" /><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-620-usmle-msk-knee-and-hip.mp3\">https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-620-usmle-msk-knee-and-hip.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-620-usmle-msk-knee-and-hip.mp3\">Audio Download</a></p>\n\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-content -->\n\t</article><!-- #post-## -->\n\n<article id=\"post-51409\" class=\"post-51409 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-anatomy-usmle-step-1 category-emergency-medicine-shelf category-family-medicine-shelf category-medicine-usmle-step-2 category-medicine-shelf category-musculoskeletal-and-dermatology-usmle-step-1 category-musculoskeletal-and-dermatology-usmle-step-3 category-neurology-shelf category-podcast category-shelf-exams category-usmle-step-1 category-usmle-step-2-ck category-usmle-step-3\">\n\t<header class=\"entry-header\">\n\t\t<h1 class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/08/13/dip-ep-619-usmle-msk-series-elbow-neck-back/\" rel=\"bookmark\">DIP Ep 619: USMLE MSK Series (Elbow, Neck,&nbsp;Back)</a></h1>\t</header><!-- .entry-header -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n\t\t\t<span class=\"posted-on\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/08/13/dip-ep-619-usmle-msk-series-elbow-neck-back/\" rel=\"bookmark\"><time class=\"entry-date published\" datetime=\"2025-08-13T07:33:59-04:00\">August 13, 2025</time></a></span><span class=\"byline\"><span class=\"author vcard\"><span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><a class=\"url fn n\" href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/author/divineinterventionpodcast/\">divineinterventionpodcast</a></span></span>\t\t\t<span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><span class=\"comments-link\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/08/13/dip-ep-619-usmle-msk-series-elbow-neck-back/#respond\">Leave a comment</a></span>\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-content\">\n\t\t<p>There are so many ways our friends at the NBMEs test musculoskeletal pathologies. In this podcast, I discuss the elbow, neck, and back. I emphasize the specific things you need to know along with the different &#8220;decision permutations&#8221; that throw people off on the exam. <em><strong>Very, very, very HY</strong></em> to know this stuff especially for the recent exams.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-51409-7\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-619-msk-elbow-neck-and-back.mp3?_=7\" /><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-619-msk-elbow-neck-and-back.mp3\">https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-619-msk-elbow-neck-and-back.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-619-msk-elbow-neck-and-back.mp3\">Audio Download</a></p>\n\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-content -->\n\t</article><!-- #post-## -->\n\n<article id=\"post-50518\" class=\"post-50518 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-podcast category-rapid-review-usmle-step-2 category-usmle-step-2-ck category-usmle-step-3\">\n\t<header class=\"entry-header\">\n\t\t<h1 class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/08/06/dip-ep-618-usmle-step-2-3-rapid-review-series-128/\" rel=\"bookmark\">DIP Ep 618: USMLE Step 2/3 Rapid Review Series&nbsp;128</a></h1>\t</header><!-- .entry-header -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n\t\t\t<span class=\"posted-on\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/08/06/dip-ep-618-usmle-step-2-3-rapid-review-series-128/\" rel=\"bookmark\"><time class=\"entry-date published\" datetime=\"2025-08-06T06:57:37-04:00\">August 6, 2025</time></a></span><span class=\"byline\"><span class=\"author vcard\"><span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><a class=\"url fn n\" href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/author/divineinterventionpodcast/\">divineinterventionpodcast</a></span></span>\t\t\t<span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><span class=\"comments-link\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/08/06/dip-ep-618-usmle-step-2-3-rapid-review-series-128/#respond\">Leave a comment</a></span>\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-content\">\n\t\t<p>In this podcast, I continue the rapid review series for the USMLE Step 2/3 exams by discussing a host of unusual &#8220;concept variants&#8221; that show up on the exams these days. These are concepts you know, but presented in a fashion you may not be used to. This is something that is done a lot these days that really throws students off. Get used to it.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-50518-8\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-618-step-2-and-3-rr-series-128.mp3?_=8\" /><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-618-step-2-and-3-rr-series-128.mp3\">https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-618-step-2-and-3-rr-series-128.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-618-step-2-and-3-rr-series-128.mp3\">Audio Download</a></p>\n\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-content -->\n\t</article><!-- #post-## -->\n\n<article id=\"post-50375\" class=\"post-50375 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-podcast\">\n\t<header class=\"entry-header\">\n\t\t<h1 class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/08/01/dip-ep-617-how-to-match-into-internal-medicine-a-detailed-guide/\" rel=\"bookmark\">DIP Ep 617: How To Match Into Internal Medicine (A Detailed&nbsp;Guide)</a></h1>\t</header><!-- .entry-header -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n\t\t\t<span class=\"posted-on\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/08/01/dip-ep-617-how-to-match-into-internal-medicine-a-detailed-guide/\" rel=\"bookmark\"><time class=\"entry-date published\" datetime=\"2025-08-01T08:12:34-04:00\">August 1, 2025</time></a></span><span class=\"byline\"><span class=\"author vcard\"><span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><a class=\"url fn n\" href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/author/divineinterventionpodcast/\">divineinterventionpodcast</a></span></span>\t\t\t<span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><span class=\"comments-link\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/08/01/dip-ep-617-how-to-match-into-internal-medicine-a-detailed-guide/#respond\">Leave a comment</a></span>\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-content\">\n\t\t<p>In this podcast, I go into very detailed specifics on how to match into IM. I discuss the different parts of the ERAS application and things you need to take note of as you put all the different parts together. Well worth a listen if you&#8217;re applying IM (or really most other related specialties).</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-50375-9\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-617-matching-im.mp3?_=9\" /><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-617-matching-im.mp3\">https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-617-matching-im.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/dip-ep-617-matching-im.mp3\">Audio Download</a></p>\n\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-content -->\n\t</article><!-- #post-## -->\n\n<article id=\"post-50224\" class=\"post-50224 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-neurology-shelf category-podcast category-rapid-review-usmle-step-2 category-usmle-step-2-ck category-usmle-step-3\">\n\t<header class=\"entry-header\">\n\t\t<h1 class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/07/28/dip-ep-616-usmle-step-2-3-rapid-review-series-127-more-basic-sciences/\" rel=\"bookmark\">DIP Ep 616: USMLE Step 2/3 Rapid Review Series 127 (More Basic&nbsp;Sciences)</a></h1>\t</header><!-- .entry-header -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n\t\t\t<span class=\"posted-on\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/07/28/dip-ep-616-usmle-step-2-3-rapid-review-series-127-more-basic-sciences/\" rel=\"bookmark\"><time class=\"entry-date published\" datetime=\"2025-07-28T08:01:55-04:00\">July 28, 2025</time></a></span><span class=\"byline\"><span class=\"author vcard\"><span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><a class=\"url fn n\" href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/author/divineinterventionpodcast/\">divineinterventionpodcast</a></span></span>\t\t\t<span class=\"sep\"> ~ </span><span class=\"comments-link\"><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.com/2025/07/28/dip-ep-616-usmle-step-2-3-rapid-review-series-127-more-basic-sciences/#respond\">Leave a comment</a></span>\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-content\">\n\t\t<p>The NBMEs have become relentless in integrating more and more basic sciences on the USMLE Step 2CK/3 exams. In this podcast, I discuss a large number of basic science concepts that routinely show up on the exam (vignettes, integrations, and contextual information).</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-50224-10\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/dip-ep-616-rr-127-step-2-and-3.mp3?_=10\" /><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/dip-ep-616-rr-127-step-2-and-3.mp3\">https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/dip-ep-616-rr-127-step-2-and-3.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><a href=\"https://divineinterventionpodcasts.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/dip-ep-616-rr-127-step-2-and-3.mp3\">Audio Download</a></p>\n\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-content -->\n\t</article><!-- #post-## -->\n<title>Understand concepts in medicine so you can solve problems for patients (and do well on your exams!)</title>\n<meta name='robots' content='max-image-preview:large' />\n\n<!-- Async WordPress.com Remote Login -->\n<script id=\"wpcom_remote_login_js\">\nvar wpcom_remote_login_extra_auth = '';\nfunction wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_id( element_id ) {\n\tvar dom_node = document.getElementById( element_id );\n\tif ( dom_node ) { dom_node.parentNode.removeChild( dom_node ); }\n}\nfunction wpcom_remote_login_remove_dom_node_classes( class_name ) {\n\tvar dom_nodes = document.querySelectorAll( '.' + class_name );\n\tfor ( var i = 0; i < dom_nodes.length; i++ ) {\n\t\tdom_nodes[ i ].parentNode.remov